.TH "tuner_lookup" 9 "tuner_lookup" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tuner_lookup \- Seek for tuner adapters
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" tuner_lookup
.BI "(struct i2c_adapter *adap "  ","
.BI "struct tuner **radio "  ","
.BI "struct tuner **tv "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adap" 12
i2c_adapter struct
.IP "radio" 12
pointer to be filled if the adapter is radio
.IP "tv" 12
pointer to be filled if the adapter is TV
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Search for existing radio and/or TV tuners on the given I2C adapter,
discarding demod-only adapters (tda9887).

Note that when this function is called from tuner_probe you can be
certain no other devices will be added/deleted at the same time, I2C
core protects against that.
